title: Guns.N.Roses-Rocket.Queen-j.sin.fat.labs
description:
Included is a cover of the Guns N' Roses song: 
"Rocket Queen" 
sung by a brand new artist called "jsin". 
And an original song off his next album, Born, set for release 2009, called:
"Inside"

All material recorded at FatLabs studio, 2008
by Producer: Vikas Kohli 

www.jsinisrockmusic.com
www.fatlabs.com

jsin has recently been featured in editions of both South Asian Living Magazine and Anokhi Magazine.
jsin has recently hit the stage at RBC's DesiFEST 2008 at Yonge/Dundas
Square and at the Rogers' MMM festival at Exhibition Place.

"Working with jsin reminds me of what rock is supposed to be.  Swagger, and honesty
that slams you in the face.  You can hear the grit in the music and
feel it when he performs," said jsin's producer, Vikas Kohli of Fatlabs.  jsin's
'Vulgar Hypocrisy' will be featured on Versailles Record's "Wicked
Garden: A Millennium Tribute to Stone Temple Pilots' Bonus CD and will
include current/former members of Concrete Blonde, Black Sabbath, Racer
X, Kiss, Megadeth, Badlands, Alice Cooper  Band,
Fuel, Surgical Steel, Circle Jerks, Slash's Snakepit, Warrant,
Steelheart, Michael Shanker Group, L.A. Guns, Machine Head, Ratt, WASP,
Quiet Riot, and others. jsin's 'You Never Know' was featured on the Toronto Independent Music Awards Compilation CD in July of 2008
